IRS990.Desc: MY HEALTHFIRST - HEALTHIER KIDS FOUNDATION PILOTED A 5TH GRADE MENTAL HEALTH SCREENING PROGRAM TO IDENTIFY CHILDREN WITH BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CONCERNS AND ASSIST THEIR PARENTS IN ACCESSING AVAILABLE CARE THROUGH LOCAL PROVIDERS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: DENTALFIRST - THE DENTALFIRST PROGRAM SCREENS CHILDREN FOR DENTAL ISSUES AND PROVIDES FOLLOW UP TO THOSE PARENTS WHOSE CHILDREN'S RESULTS INDICATE THAT THEY HAVE UNTREATED DENTAL ISSUES.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: HEARINGFIRST - A PROGRAM THAT USES OTOACOUSTIC EMISSION ("OAE") SCREENING DEVICES TO SCREEN CHILDREN FOR UNDETECTED HEARING ISSUES AND ASSIST THEM WITH OBTAINING HEARING SERVICES AND TREATMENT.

ProgSrvcAccomActyOtherGrp.Desc: VISIONFIRST PROGRAM - A PROGRAM THAT USES HIGH-TECH, PHOTO OPTIC SCAN CAMERAS TO SCREEN CHILDREN FOR UNDETECTED VISION ISSUES AND ASSIST THEM WITH ACCESSING FOLLOW-UP VISION SERVICES AND PRESCRIBED TREATMENT.10 STEPS TO A HEALTHIER YOU! - A FREE, FIVE-CLASS SERIES FOR PARENTS THAT FOCUSES ON INTEGRATING HEALTHY LIFESTYLES WITHIN THEIR HOMES TO PREVENT OR REDUCE CHILDHOOD AND ADOLESCENT OBESITY.COMMUNITYFIRST - OUR COMMITMENT TO SERVICE AND SUPPORTING OTHER AGENCIES, APPLYING OUR LEADERSHIP CAPABILITIES TO BOOST POSITIVE OUTCOMES ACROSS THE COMMUNITY. SMILEFIRST - INTERACTIVE ORAL EDUCATION WORKSHOPS THAT TEACH STUDENTS ABOUT KEEPING GOOD DENTAL HYGIENE. PREGNANTFIRST -ASSIST FUTURE PARENTS/PREGNANT PERSONS IN ACCESSING DENTAL TREATMENT THROUGH INDIVIDUALIZED CARE COORDINATION.COPE - A PROGRAM THAT IDENTIFIES UNINSURED CHILDREN AND ASSISTS THEIR PARENTS IN ENROLLING THEIR CHILDREN INTO SUBSIDIZED HEALTH COVERAGE. BABY GATEWAY - ENROLLS NEWBORNS INTO MEDI-CAL, ENSURES THEY SECURE A MEDICAL HOME, AND PROVIDES PARENTING AND HEALTH RESOURCES BEFORE BEING DISCHARGED FROM THE HOSPITAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: HKF EVALUATES ITS UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS AND WILL RECOGNIZE A LOSS CONTINGENCY WHEN IT IS PROBABLE THAT A LIABILITY HAS BEEN INCURRED AS OF THE DATE OF THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND THE AMOUNT OF THE LOSS CAN BE REASONABLY ESTIMATED. AS OF JUNE 30, 2023, MANAGEMENT DID NOT IDENTIFY ANY UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS.

A SMALL PERCENTAGE OF THE BONUS FOR THE CEO AND THE DIRECTOR OF PROGRAMS BONUS IS CALCULATED ON THE ORGANIZATIONS REVENUE INCREASE. THE MAJORITY OF THE BONUS IS CALCULATED ON INCREASING THE NUMBER OF PARTICIPANTS IN EACH OF THE ORGANIZATIONS PROGRAMS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CEO OF HEALTHIER KIDS FOUNDATION, WHO IS ALSO A VOTING MEMBER OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, REVIEWS THE IRS FORM 990. THE BOARD-APPOINTED AUDIT COMMITTEE, CONSISTING OF ALL VOTING MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS, REVIEWS THE FORM 990 AND PROVIDES APPROVAL PRIOR TO FILING THE DOCUMENT. THE APPROVED IRS FORM 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS PRIOR TO SUBMITTING IT TO THE IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: A STAFF MEMBER DISTRIBUTES A CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENT TO EACH BOARD MEMBER ON AN ANNUAL BASIS AND ONCE NEW MEMBERS ARE APPOINTED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMPENSATION COMMITTEE REVIEWS ALL COMPENSATION AND FOR THE DETERMINATION OF THE CEO'S COMPENSATION USES AN OUTSIDE COMPENSATION STUDY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: HEALTHIER KIDS FOUNDATION POSTS ITS AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ON WWW.GUIDESTAR.ORG. IT ALSO DISTRIBUTES ITS AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND GOVERNING DOCUMENTS TO ITS BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND FUNDERS. WHEN REQUESTED, HEALTHIER KIDS FOUNDATION DISTRIBUTES CONFLICT OF INTEREST STATEMENTS TO ENTITIES AND/OR INDIVIDUALS.
CONTRACTORS: PROGRAM SERVICE EXPENSES 673,596. MANAGEMENT AND GENERAL EXPENSES 12,404. FUNDRAISING EXPENSES 3,230. TOTAL EXPENSES 689,230.
THE PROCESS FOR AN AUDIT COMMITTEE TO REVIEW THE ANNUAL 990 FORM HAS NOT CHANGED FROM PRIOR YEAR.
